.admin-registry.my-3
  %header.admin-registry__head
    %span.admin-registry__title
      %i.fa-solid.fa-user-secret{'aria-hidden' => 'true'}
      Impersonation
    .admin-registry__head-actions
      %span.admin-registry__subtitle
        %i.fa-solid.fa-lock{'aria-hidden' => 'true'}
        Admin-only

  .p-3
    %p.text-muted.small.mb-3
      Operate as another user. <strong>Act as</strong> attributes any deposits or edits wholly to that user, with your own identity recorded in the audit trail; <strong>View as</strong> is read-only and shows exactly what they can see. A persistent banner marks the session, which ends on an attempted write during View-as (the write is blocked) or after 30 minutes idle.

    = form_tag admin_act_as_path, method: :post,
               data: { controller: 'impersonation-search',
                       impersonation_search_url_value: admin_impersonation_recipients_path } do
      .mb-3.position-relative
        = label_tag :impersonation_query, 'Target user', class: 'form-label'
        %input#impersonation_query.form-control{ type: 'text', autocomplete: 'off',
          placeholder: 'Search by name, or enter a NUID…',
          data: { impersonation_search_target: 'query', action: 'input->impersonation-search#search' } }
        = hidden_field_tag :nuid, nil, data: { impersonation_search_target: 'nuid' }
        .list-group.inbox-typeahead{ hidden: true, data: { impersonation_search_target: 'results' } }
      .d-flex.gap-2
        = submit_tag 'Act as', name: 'mode', class: 'btn btn-danger', formaction: admin_act_as_path
        = submit_tag 'View as', name: 'mode', class: 'btn btn-warning', formaction: admin_view_as_path
